Homework!

/* 
In order to learn this subject of programming well, you have to practice:

Popcorn hack 1: operations with variables

Popcorn hack 2: Make 2 variables x, and y. Compute 3 different operations and log it into the console with console.log();

Final Task: Build a system of functions that represent different mathematical expressions. Each of these functions will perform a different mathematical operation (ex: add, subtract). Make at least 5 of these different functions.
*/
/* 
Popcorn Hack 1 (Progress Check)

Part 1:
Create two variables, val1 and val2. 
Set val1 to 8 and val2 to 4.  
Then compute the expression:

(val1 * val2) + (val1 / 2)

This expression should equal 36.

Part 2:
Using the same variables, create a new variable called totalValue.  
Set totalValue equal to:

val1 / val2 + 2 ** 3

Then compute the final expression:

(totalValue + 20) - val1 ** 2 / 4

Write your code below:

// put your popcorn hack 1 code here:
*/

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Code Runner</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; padding: 20px; }
    textarea { width: 100%; height: 200px; font-family: monospace; }
    #output { background: #111; color: #0f0; padding: 10px; margin-top: 10px; min-height: 60px; white-space: pre-wrap; }
    button { margin-top: 10px; padding: 8px 16px; font-size: 14px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h2>Code Runner</h2>
  <p>Type your JavaScript code below and click "Run Code".</p>

  <textarea id="code">// write your JavaScript here</textarea>
  <br>
  <button onclick="runCode()">Run Code</button>

  <h3>Output:</h3>
  <div id="output"></div>

  <script>
    function runCode() {
      const code = document.getElementById('code').value;
      const outputDiv = document.getElementById('output');
      outputDiv.textContent = '';

      const originalLog = console.log;
      console.log = function (...args) {
        outputDiv.textContent += args.join(' ') + '\n';
        originalLog.apply(console, args);
      };

      try {
        new Function(code)();
      } catch (err) {
        outputDiv.textContent += 'Error: ' + err.message;
      }

      console.log = originalLog;
    }
  </script>

</body>
</html>

// Part 1
let val1 = 8;
let val2 = 4;

console.log((val1 * val2) + (val1 / 2)); 
// Expected output: 36

// Part 2
let totalValue = val1 / val2 + 2 ** 3;

console.log((totalValue + 20) - val1 ** 2 / 4);







